ng view of the surrounding region because it is situated at around 6400 feet above mean sea level. However, climbing to the top of the waterfall is a very difficult one. The gigantic obstacle the travellers meet makes it impossible for even the most dedicated trekkers to continue their journey. The highest point of the mountain is called Vellarimala. Although the height of the waterfall is fairly impressive, the amount of water and the flow rate is not quite as strong. The monsoon is the finest time to go to the waterfall since the volume of water would be high enough to offer you a great view of the falls. The waterfall is best visited during the monsoon. In any other case, you will be able to see a stream with a very slow flow. You may walk the remaining six kilometres to reach the peak of the hill if you are an individual who enjoys going on hikes. The journey often starts at the beautiful Muthappanpuzha village, which is very close to the Thiruvambady region of the Kozhikode district. If you are going to the waterfalls with your family, you should not go for the hike since it will be highly inconvenient for everyone in your group. 7. Kozhikode Beach One of the most popular destinations in Calicut/Kozhikode is Kozhikode Beach, often known as Calicut Beach. This beach can be found on the Malabar coast of India. Watching the breathtaking sunset at this stunning beach is a popular activity for out-of-town visitors and residents. Take a leisurely walk down the beach, or kick back and watch the sun sink slowly into the water on the horizon. Early morning is the best time to visit this location if one is interested in testing their chances of seeing dolphins. The months of October through March are perfect for a trip to the beach. 8. Taj Green Cove Resort & Spa Kovalam The Taj Green Cove Resort & Spa in Kovalam is one of the most magnificent resorts around Kozhikode. It is situated on a small hill and offers a breathtaking view of the Arabian Sea. This is a huge resort